info.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 09 at 1:40AM PST until January 09 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Eureka
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST THIS MORNING... * WHAT...South winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 60 mph. The strongest winds are expected on exposed ridges, coastal headlands, and along the north shore of Clear Lake. Some of the most exposed ridges could see gusts in excess of 65 mph. * WHERE...Coastal Humboldt, Coastal Del Norte, Trinity, Lake, and Mendocino counties. * WHEN...Until 10 AM PST Monday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
